title.narrative: Protection and resilience of women and girls in Rohingya refugee camps and in host communities are enhanced

description.narrative: This outcome will focus on strengthening the capacity of the humanitarian practitioners working in natural disaster response as well as in refugee crisis to undertake need assessments in gender responsive way. It aims to enhance+D28 the capacity of the humanitarian community including practitioners and officials to design, plan and implement gender responsive humanitarian action. More specifically, this outcome focuses on providing safe shelter and necessary life-saving information to the displaced Rohingya women and girls, especially meeting the emergency needs for the most vulnerable women and girls (e.g. elderly, pregnant and lactating mothers, traumatized, lonely mothers, and abandoned/ unattended/ orphaned girls), while ensuring that they are actively engaged in the humanitarian operation.
